# OpenFugu

**Sakana shipped Fugu as a closed API. We open-sourced the full stack — router + conductor — for ~$50.**

OpenFugu is a faithful open-source reimplementation of [Sakana Fugu](https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.21228): a two-tier LLM orchestration system exposed as a single OpenAI-compatible API.

| Mode | Paper basis | Behavior |
|------|-------------|----------|
| **`openfugu`** | Fugu §3.1 (simplified Trinity) | Fast hidden-state routing → one worker per turn |
| **`openfugu-ultra`** | Conductor (ICLR 2026) | Multi-agent workflows up to 5 steps |

> Not affiliated with Sakana AI. Sakana does not release trained Fugu weights — OpenFugu provides the architecture, training pipelines, and inference runtime so you can train and deploy on your own worker pool.

## Architecture

```
You → /v1/chat/completions → openfugu | openfugu-ultra
                                    ↓           ↓
                              TinyRouter    Conductor
                              (SFT+CMA-ES)  (GRPO)
                                    ↓           ↓
                              Worker Pool (LiteLLM: OpenAI, Anthropic, Ollama, OpenRouter...)
```

## Quickstart (5 minutes)

```bash
python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Configure workers in config/default.yaml, set API keys
export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

openfugu serve
# → http://localhost:8080
```

```bash
curl http://localhost:8080/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"model":"openfugu","messages":[{"role":"user","content":"Hello"}]}'
```

Every response includes `openfugu` metadata showing which worker was chosen and why — unlike Sakana's black box.

## Drop-in Sakana replacement

```python
from openai import OpenAI

client = OpenAI(
    base_url="http://localhost:8080/v1",
    api_key="optional",
)

# Was: model="fugu"
client.chat.completions.create(model="openfugu", messages=[...])

# Was: model="fugu-ultra-20260615"
client.chat.completions.create(model="openfugu-ultra", messages=[...])
```

## Models

| Model ID | Sakana equivalent | Latency | Best for |
|----------|-------------------|---------|----------|
| `openfugu` | `fugu` | ~1 model call | Chat, coding, everyday tasks |
| `openfugu-ultra` | `fugu-ultra-20260615` | Multi-step | Hard reasoning, multi-agent tasks |
| `auto` | — | Varies | Auto-dispatch by complexity |

## Training

Full pipelines included — no closed weights required:

```bash
pip install -e ".[train]"

# Router: label collection → SFT (KL soft targets) → sep-CMA-ES
python scripts/collect_router_labels.py
openfugu train-router --stage all

# Conductor: GRPO
openfugu train-conductor --smoke   # verify pipeline
openfugu train-conductor            # full run
```

See [docs/TRAINING.md](docs/TRAINING.md) for GPU requirements and hyperparameters.

## $50 self-host path

| Item | Cost |
|------|------|
| Ollama (local worker) | $0 |
| OpenRouter credit | ~$20 |
| Lambda H100 4hr (SFT) | ~$30 |
| **Total** | **~$50** |

Details: [docs/SETUP.md](docs/SETUP.md)

